fix(orchestrator): PR #328 follow-up — register transport_failure + Option B warning + test coverage (#329)

Real bug fix + 4 follow-ups from PR #328 pre-merge consensus 84870901-0136416f.

The headline change: transport_failure was missing from VALID_CONSENSUS_SIGNALS, so PR #328's fail-closed signal emit was being silently dropped by validateSignal. New Test 4 now asserts the row lands in agent-performance.jsonl. Both prior consensus rounds (0df2a87c-9c8049e4:f7 and 84870901:f7) flagged this;

chore(ci): bump actions/upload-artifact to @v6 (Node 24)

@v5 still ships on Node 20 — caught by the next workflow run after the prior
bump. v6 is the first major built on Node 24.
